## 🗄️ 2. NoSQL Database Schema Design (MongoDB)

Here is how the data structures are designed to reflect clean document-modeling practices:

### 1. `gold_rates` Collection
Stores the current prices of gold. Keeping this in a separate document makes it easy to read and update daily.
```json
{
  "_id": "current_gold_rates",
  "rates": {
    "gold_24k_per_gram": 9500,
    "gold_22k_per_gram": 8700,
    "gold_18k_per_gram": 7125
  },
  "lastUpdated": "2026-05-19T14:10:00Z"
}
```

### 2. `inventory` Collection
Demonstrates flexible schemas and embedded subdocuments (gems).
```json
{
  "_id": "ObjectId('...')",
  "sku": "RNG-DIA-092",
  "name": "Classic Solitaire Diamond Ring",
  "category": "Ring",
  "metalType": "gold_22k",
  "metalWeightGrams": 4.8,
  "makingCharge": 12000,
  
  "gemstones": [
    {
      "gemType": "Diamond",
      "carats": 0.35,
      "cut": "Brilliant",
      "clarity": "VVS1",
      "cost": 45000
    }
  ],
  
  "status": "In_Showcase", // "In_Showcase", "Sold", "Melted"
  "enteredStockDate": "2026-01-10T12:00:00Z",
  "specifications": {
    "ringSize": "14",
    "certificateNo": "GIA-88930"
  }
}
```

### 3. `orders` Collection
Records manual transactions. Denormalizes item details so historical sales records remain static even if the product catalog or daily gold rates change.
```json
{
  "_id": "ObjectId('...')",
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-2026-0042",
  "saleDate": "2026-05-19T19:40:00Z",
  "customerName": "Kamal Perera",
  "customerPhone": "0771234567",
  
  "items": [
    {
      "sku": "RNG-DIA-092",
      "name": "Classic Solitaire Diamond Ring",
      "metalWeightGrams": 4.8,
      "goldRateApplied": 8700, 
      "makingChargeApplied": 12000,
      "gemstoneValueApplied": 45000,
      "itemTotal": 98760
    }
  ],
  
  "goldExchange": {
    "exchangedWeightGrams": 2.5,
    "exchangedRatePerGram": 8000,
    "discountValue": 20000
  },
  
  "paymentMethod": "Cash", // Cash, Card, Hybrid
  "subtotal": 98760,
  "discount": 20000,
  "finalAmountPaid": 78760
}
```

