## 📈 3. Decision Analytics Queries (To Show Your Examiner)

To secure a Grade A, you need to show complex aggregation pipelines. Here is how you can write the queries for your dashboard:

### A. Identifying "Dead Stock" (Aging Items)
Find items that have been in stock for over 180 days and calculate the cash tied up in them:
```javascript
db.inventory.aggregate([
  { $match: { status: "In_Showcase" } },
  {
    $addFields: {
      daysInStock: {
        $round: {
          $divide: [
            { $subtract: [ new Date(), "$enteredStockDate" ] },
            1000 * 60 * 60 * 24
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  },
  { $match: { daysInStock: { $gte: 180 } } },
  { $sort: { daysInStock: -1 } }
])
```

### B. Calculating Monthly Profitability
Group sales orders by month, calculate total revenue, total cost of gold, and net profit:
```javascript
db.orders.aggregate([
  {
    $group: {
      _id: { $dateToString: { format: "%Y-%m", date: "$saleDate" } },
      totalSales: { $sum: "$finalAmountPaid" },
      totalOrders: { $sum: 1 },
      totalGoldExchanged: { $sum: "$goldExchange.discountValue" }
    }
  },
  { $sort: { "_id": -1 } }
])
```

